{"body": "Is there any particular reason why the semantics --edge has change to mean 3-2 stable?  For example, when I run the command 'rails new my app --edge', I was expecting to see the following within the Gemfile:\n\ngem 'rails',     :git => 'git://github.com/rails/rails.git'\n\ninstead of \n\ngem 'rails',     :git => 'git://github.com/rails/rails.git', :branch => '3-2-stable'\n\nSo, what's the appropriate syntax for generating a rails application based on the latest code base?", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/6619035", "created_at": "2012-06-28T00:13:57Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/4920#issuecomment-6619035", "updated_at": "2012-06-28T00:13:57Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 4920, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/conradwt/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/conradwt/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/conradwt/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/conradwt", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/conradwt/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/conradwt", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/conradwt/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/40db9e75b3f5899258e3bdc0c9210154?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fb09e9b8f288432a0628bf7a6f1b8ed42.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/conradwt/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/conradwt/received_events", "gravatar_id": "40db9e75b3f5899258e3bdc0c9210154", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/conradwt/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "conradwt", "type": "User", "id": 20219, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/conradwt/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52381f3ebd3543c15100e745"}, "id": 6619035, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/4920"}
